category: BUILDING A NEW WORD
category comment: 

clue: Poet Robert stops by the woods on a snowy evening to chomp on a synonym for chomp & develops this chilly condition

response: frostbite

clue: An auto picks up golfer Nicklaus to become this crime

response: carjack

clue: To bound or leap drinks Macallan to play this kids' playground game

response: hopscotch

clue: A set of squares like our game board adds a fastener to get nothing done politically

response: gridlock

clue: A harbor for a ship docks with a loose coat or robe to be this type of word, like spork or mockumentary

response: portmanteau

